HEADWORD: Pubic
<hw>Pu"bic</hw> <pr>(p⟦umac⟧"b⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the pubes; in the region of
the pubes; <as>as, the <ex>pubic</ex> bone; the <ex>pubic</ex> region,
or the lower part of the hypogastric region</as>. See
<er>Pubes</er>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Of or pertaining to the
pubis.</def>⟦br⟧
